# Design System (src/app/design-system/)

Use the project design system for all UI. It provides tokens for colors, typography, spacing, radius, and shadows.

## Files

- **theme.css** – `@theme` block: fonts (Outfit/Switzer), spacing, radius, shadows, base colors (brand, gray, error, warning, success), semantic tokens (fg, bg, border, text).
- **colors.css** – Theme variants: `.untitled-brand` (default purple), `.untitled-gray-light-mode`, `.untitled-error`, `.untitled-success`. Applied on `html`.
- **typography.css** – Prose styles and heading/body scaling.

## Color Tokens

### Brand palette (default: purple)

- **Scale:** `brand-25` … `brand-950` (e.g. `bg-brand-500`, `text-brand-600`)
- **Semantic:** `fg-primary`, `fg-secondary`, `fg-tertiary`, `border-primary`, `border-secondary`, `bg-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-brand-solid`

### Shadcn compatibility

- Use `background`, `foreground`, `muted`, `muted-foreground`, `border`, `primary`, `secondary`, `accent`, `destructive`, `ring` where shadcn expects them. These are mapped in `globals.css`.

### Rules

- **Prefer design tokens** – Use `bg-brand-500`, `text-fg-secondary`, `border-border`, etc., instead of `zinc-*`, raw hex, or `indigo-*` / `sky-*`.
- **Use `.page-container`** for section wrappers (horizontal padding scale: 16px → 32px → 64px).
- **Typography:** `font-heading` (Outfit) for headings, `font-body` (Switzer) for body. See [typography-typescale.mdc](typography-typescale.mdc).

## Theme variants

Add a class to `html` to change the brand palette: `untitled-brand`, `untitled-gray-light-mode`, `untitled-error`, `untitled-success`.
